  "data": [
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.1",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "1",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.1",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Her prophet - So called, false prophets. Light - Unstable and inconstant. Violence to the law - Wresting it by perverse interpretation.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.2",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "2",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.2",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "In the midst - Observing all. Not do iniquity - He will judge them righteously. Every morning - Daily he discovers his displeasure against the wicked. Faileth not - Lets no season slip to convince them, by public and visible punishments. The unjust - But the wicked Jews proceed without shame, and without fear.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.3",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "3",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.3",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The nations - Of old, the Canaanites, lastly the ten tribes, and later yet, the Assyrians.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.4",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "4",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.4",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "I said - I thought (speaking after the manner of men). Thou - O Jerusalem. Fear me - For the many and great judgments executed upon others. I punished them - In some measure.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.5",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "5",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.5",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Therefore - Since you will not be amended. Wait ye - Attend my resolution. Until - Until I rise up to destroy first, and next to take the spoil. Upon them - The incorrigible Jews. Devoured - Consumed as if burnt up. My jealousy - That jealousy wherewith God is jealous for his own glory.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.6",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "6",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.6",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "A pure language - I will give them a pure way of worshipping me, the issue of a pure heart.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.7",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "7",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.7",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "My dispersed - The praying remnant of the scattered Jews shall return to their own land, and bring themselves an offering unto the Lord.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.8",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "8",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.8",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Thy doings - Thy sins formerly committed. In thy pride - Proud formalists. No more be haughty - Ye shall no more boast, because of the city, or the temple.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.9",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "9",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.9",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Of thee - In Judea and Jerusalem.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.10",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "10",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.10",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Shall feed - Shall enjoy peace and plenty.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.12",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "12",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.12",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Taken away - Abolished, and put an end to the judgments thy sins brought upon thee. Thine enemy - The Babylonian. Is in the midst - He is returned to redeem and govern thee. Any more - While thy carriage is as becomes my presence with thee, thou shalt neither fear, nor feel the like evils.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.1.15",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 1,
      "verse_range": "15",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.1.15",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Sorrowful - That mourn their distance from the solemn worship of God. Who are of thee - Thy children. Reproach - The taunts of their enemies.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.1",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "1",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.1",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "A praise - So the universal church of the first - born will be, in the great day. And then the Israel of God be made a name and a praise to all eternity.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.3",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "3",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.3",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "This - So the prophet triumphs over her. There is none - None like me, or that can contend with me.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.4",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "4",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.4",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Son - Adoptive son to Shealtiel, being of the royal line, but by nature, son of Pedaiah. Governor - Appointed to this by the Persian king, over the remnant returned out of Babylon. Joshua - A type of the great deliverer; one Joshua leads them into Canaan, another restores the temple.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.7",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "7",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.7",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Ceiled - Arched and richly adorned.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.9",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "9",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.9",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Have not enough - But what you eat doth not nourish or satisfy you. Are not filled - Your water quenches not your thirst, your wine does not revive your spirit. None warm - You have no comfort therein. With holes - Loses all his labour.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.11",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "11",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.11",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Take pleasure - I will accept your offerings, and hear your prayers. Glorified - Shew my majesty and account myself glorified by you also.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.12",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "12",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.12",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Came to little - But it answered not the expectation. I did blow - I blasted it. Ye run - You with eagerness carry on your own particular buildings.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.13",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "13",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.13",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Is stayed - God hath forbidden them, to drop down dew.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.14",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "14",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.14",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "Upon men - The very blood, and constitutions of men were changed, and many diseases afflicted them.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.16",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "16",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.16",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "In the Lord's message - ln the words of his master. The people - The whole assembly.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.17",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "17",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.17",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "The Lord of hosts - By which name he delights to be known among the returned captives; and it was a name best suited to their present state, compassed on all hands with enemies.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "entry_id": "wesley-notes-bible.Hag.2.22",
      "book": "Haggai",
      "book_osis": "Hag",
      "book_number": 37,
      "chapter": 2,
      "verse_range": "22",
      "verse_range_osis": "Hag.2.22",
      "verse_text": null,
      "commentary_text": "That saw - Near fourscore years ago. This house - The temple built by Solomon.",
      "summary": null,
      "summary_review_status": "withheld",
      "cross_references": [],
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ]
}
